First load the master dataset and the day records list into the environment
```{r}
load("/Users/caleb/OneDrive - University of Waterloo/Research/code/reader_merge_code/rdata/join.rdata")
load("/Users/caleb/OneDrive - University of Waterloo/Research/code/reader_merge_code/rdata/nl_day_records.rdata")
```

Load relevant packages
```{r}
library(lubridate)
library(rlang)
library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
```

Create dataframe with only the known aged individuals from Salmonier Nature Park

```{r}
snpknownage<-subset(join,loc == "snp" & agetype =="exactly", select = c("pit", "loc" , "age" , "box", "year" , "pityr", "pitymd"))
snpknownage$month = month(snpknownage$pitymd)
```

```{r}
day_roostnum$pitage = as.numeric(day_roostnum$pityr) - as.numeric(day_roostnum$year)
```

Create an object of both roost metrics joined
```{r}
roostnum$pityr = as.character(roostnum$pityr)
day_roostnum$pityr = as.character(day_roostnum$pityr)
colnames(day_roostnum)[2] <- "num_day_box"
both_use = left_join(roostnum , day_roostnum , by = c("pit" , "pityr" ,  "month" , "year"))
both_use = both_use[!is.na(both_use$num_day_box), ]
nrow(both_use)
```

Combine the above object with the number of reads
```{r}
colnames(snpknownallcynum_reads)[2] <- "num_reads"
both_use_reads= left_join(both_use , snpknownallcynum_reads , by = c("pit" , "year" , "pityr", "month" , "pitage"))
nrow(both_use_reads)
both_use_reads
table(both_use_reads$pit , both_use_reads$month)
count_numday$pityr = as.character(count_numday$pityr)
both_use_reads_days = left_join(both_use_reads , count_numday , by = c("pit" , "pityr" , "month"))
```

Filter for individuals who were observed on at least 10 days/month observed
```{r}
both_use_reads = both_use_reads_days %>% 
  filter(num_day >= 10)

both_use_reads$num_box.x = both_use_reads$num_box
both_use_reads$num_box.y = both_use_reads$num_day_box

both_use_reads <- subset(both_use_reads, select = c(pit, num_box , month , year , pityr , pitage , num_day_box , num_reads, num_day))

colnames(both_use_reads)[2] <- "num_box"
table(both_use_reads$pit, both_use_reads$pityr)
```

Filter through a yearly filter including only individuals observed during at least 4 year
```{r}
countyearbothusereads = count(both_use_reads, pit)
fouryearbothreadsfilter = filter(countyearbothusereads, n<4)
bothusereadsyear = subset(both_use_reads, ! both_use_reads$pit  %in% fouryearbothreadsfilter$pit)
table(bothusereadsyear$year , bothusereadsyear$pit)
both_use_reads = bothusereadsyear
```

Save the final processed data file
```{r}
save(both_use_reads, file = "/Users/caleb/OneDrive - University of Waterloo/Research/code/honours_thesis/both_use_reads.RData")
```
